	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, other than sow potions, most potions dont seem that popular.  However, they can still be usefull and I've been trying to show a few people that by slipping them into sales as added bonuses in the commons.  Running specials like buy a 10 shot sow potion and get a free sample of a buff potion.  Seems to be working out ok, my sales are really up or anything but at least people are starting to notice other potions besides sow :-)<br><br>As far as the overall value of the potion, as a shaman, you can outbuff it yourself with ease at any lvl where you could make the potion but that doesn't mean someone like a troll warior can.  I've got several characters who don't naturally have spell buffs and these potions do wonders for helping your own alts get through some tough spots at times.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
